An empty exhibition hall booth draped in faded blue and yellow corporate banners, with tumbleweeds of dust bunnies rolling across the glossy floor, while in the background rival booths burst with colorful crowds and activity, rendered in a vintage 1960s advertising illustration style with muted warm tones, grainy textures, and stylized mid-century figures browsing displays, the abandoned booth sits in sharp contrast under a single spotlight creating dramatic shadows, conveying a sense of missed opportunity and corporate absence amid bustling industry competition
